   "source": [
    "# `apply_padded`\n",
    "Applies padding to an image before passing through specified function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:02.572893Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:02.572451Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.389257Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.388634Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "import scipy.ndimage as spim\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import skimage\n",
    "from edt import edt\n",
    "ps.visualization.set_mpl_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im`\n",
    "Generate a test image. Can be 2D or 3D image."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.392631Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.392382Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.797052Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.796340Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 583,
       "width": 583
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "im = np.zeros([300, 300])\n",
    "im = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im, r=20, phi=0.6) == 0\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=[6, 6])\n",
    "plt.axis(False)\n",
    "plt.imshow(im);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `func`\n",
    "A good use case is `skeletonize_3d`, which has edge artifacts that can be reduced if the image is pre-padded. It works on 2D or 3D images."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.802588Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.801816Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.805192Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.804689Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "func = skimage.morphology.skeletonize_3d"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `pad_width`\n",
    "The amount of padding to add to each axis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.807744Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:05.807483Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.182760Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.182116Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x1200 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 614,
       "width": 1184
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x1 = ps.filters.apply_padded(im=im, pad_width=1, func=func, pad_val=1)\n",
    "x2 = ps.filters.apply_padded(im=im, pad_width=100, func=func, pad_val=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 12]);\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(x1);\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title('pad_width = 1')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(x2);\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title('pad_width = 100');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It's also useful for morphological operations such as `binary_opening`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.185616Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.185300Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.189161Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.188462Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "func = skimage.morphology.binary_opening"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.192032Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.191546Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.460697Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.460214Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x1200 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 614,
       "width": 1184
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x3 = ps.filters.apply_padded(im=im, pad_width=0, func=func, pad_val=1, footprint=ps.tools.ps_disk(15))\n",
    "x4 = ps.filters.apply_padded(im=im, pad_width=50, func=func, pad_val=1, footprint=ps.tools.ps_disk(15))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 12]);\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(x3)\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title('With no padding')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(x4)\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title('With padding');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `pad_val`\n",
    "The value to be placed in padded voxels. It is almost always 1 but setting to 0 may be useful for applying a distance transform."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.463710Z",

     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:56:06.465895Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {
    "execution": {

   },
